pull_request.title: Make e2e app bits configurable
pull_request.body:
## Is there a related GitHub Issue?
No

## What is this change about?
Update end to end tests to use a configurable file for app bits instead of the hardcoded binary. By default, behavior remains the same.

## Does this PR introduce a breaking change?
No

## Acceptance Steps
Deploy korifi normally for development and run end to end tests. See that tests continue to pass and that the prebuilt node app is still being pushed by default.

Prepare a different app known to successfully build with the default builder in the assets dir like the previously used `assets/node.zip`, set the "APP_BITS_FILE" environment variable accordingly to that file, and see that the tests continue to pass while pushing that app.

## Tag your pair, your PM, and/or team
paired w/ @Birdrock

issue.title: [Feature]: builds created through the shim generate BuildWorkload resources
issue.body:
### Blockers/Dependencies

[#1002]

### Background

**As a** developer who wants to extend korifi
**I want** builds created in the API shim to be managed via BuildWorkload resources
**So that** I can use them as an extension point to implement different build workflows


### Acceptance Criteria

**GIVEN** a korifi installation on a k8s cluster
**WHEN I** create the first build for an App through the API shim (e.g. via `cf push`)
**THEN I** should see that a BuildWorkload resource is created
**AND** eventually the build information returned from the shim should show the `STAGED` state
**AND** I should be able to run the freshly built image without issues

---

**WHEN I** create a second build for the App through the API shim (e.g. via `cf push` with updated source)
**THEN I** should see that the existing BuildWorkload resource is updated
**AND** initially the build information returned from the shim should show the `STAGING` state
**AND** eventually it should show `STAGED` instead

---

**WHEN I** create a third build for the App using a package that will fail to build
**THEN I** should see that the existing BuildWorkload resource is updated
**AND** eventually the build information returned from the shim should show the `FAILED` state for the build


### Dev Notes

* **Though this work is written from the perspective of the API, the work is actually in the controllers**. We currently create kpack Images in the `CFBuild` controller, and that will now create `BuildWorkload` resources instead and watch them for status updates.
* **As part of this work, remove the existing code that directly creates kpack Image resources**. Remove the now-unnecessary RBAC rules
* Ensure that the `BuildWorkload` has an `ownerRef` for the `CFApp`
* Note that we're reusing the same `BuildWorkload` resource for every build of the same app. Each app has at most 1 `BuildWorkload` resource
* A later story will ensure that only 1 build runs at a time. For this story, assume that 2 builds for the same app will never run concurrently.

comment.body:
Tasks:
- [] CFBuild reconciler now makes/watches BuildWorkload
- [] Delete now-unused code from controllers
- [] Ensure that the e2e tests install kpack-image-builder and that they pass
